olive oil
1 packet Pearl (Israeli) Couscous
1.5 cup water
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 Cucumber
½ White Turnip
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet chicken thigh
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Garlic Aioli

• In a medium saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Toast pearl couscous,
stirring occasionally, until golden, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water and chicken-style stock powder.
Bring to the boil, then cook, uncovered, stirring
occasionally, until tender and the water is
absorbed, 10-12 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice cucumber into halfmoons. Thinly slice white turnip (see
ingredients) and baby leaves.
• In a medium bowl, combine cucumber, turnip
and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive
oil. Season with salt and pepper.

• In a second medium bowl, combine garlic & herb seasoning, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Add chicken and turn to coat.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook chicken thigh, turning occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 10-14 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked when it's no longer pink inside.

• Add baby leaves and a drizzle of olive oil to the
couscous and stir to combine. Season to taste.

• Slice the chicken.
• Divide couscous between bowls. Top with
garlicky chicken, cucumber salsa and garlic
aioli. Season with pepper to serve. Enjoy!